President Barack Obama has announced his intention to appoint several individuals to the Presidential Commission for the Study of Bioethical Issues. This commission will advise the President on bioethical issues that arise from advancements in biomedicine and related areas of science and technology. The appointees include Lonnie Ali, Anita L. Allen, Barbara Atkinson, Nita A. Farahany, Alexander G. Garza, Christine Grady, Stephen L. Hauser, Raju Kucherlapati, Nelson Michael, and Daniel Sulmasy. These individuals have diverse backgrounds and expertise in fields such as medicine, law, and philosophy. President Obama expressed gratitude for their willingness to contribute their talent and experience to the commission and looks forward to their recommendations in the future.